Description: Doug Houston Outdoors provides charter fishing trips out of Dauphin Island, Gulf Shores, and/or Orange Beach Alabama.
Full Description: At Doug Houston Outdoors Charter Fishing,, we enjoy sharing our love for fishing, Mobile Bay, and the Gulf of Mexico with others. Nothing is more rewarding than to see the smiling faces of those who have just caught a beautiful fish from the Gulf , Mobile Bay, and numerous inlets all along the Alabama Gulf Coast and to know that they are having a great time on the water. We love fishing hope you do too. Our Mobile Bay charter near shore and deep-sea fishing trips start with the captain pulling a shrimp troll for your bait while the Dolphins swim along side. Then head to the Gulf of Mexico for some line pulling- rod bending action. No Fishing License needed. We provide live bait, ice, fuel, state of the art tackle and late model vessel. All that you will need are your personal snacks/drinks, sunscreen and your camera. Charter Fishing is our specialty. Doug Houston Outdoors is a charter service based in Dauphin Island, Alabama. Captain Doug heads a team of 7 captains who are all seasoned local fishermen and tournament winners and know these waters very well. Whether you want to do some fishing on your own or spend quality time with your family, they’ve got you covered.

Full Description: Landtech began a year earlier on the Radio Shack TRS-80 Model I computer. This first system had no lower-case characters or color. This was 7 years before Microsoft would go public and more than 2 years prior to the introduction of the IBM PC, which would revolutionize the workplace. Landtech Data Corporation was incorporated in 1986. Landtech offered the first real estate settlement software for the Personal Computer. In fact, Landtech advertised in the September, 1981 issue of TITLE NEWS (ALTA) its availability on the IBM Personal Business Computer which was introduced that same year. Since those early beginnings Landtech has become the nation’s largest provider of real estate settlement software to a whole host of users engaged in the financial, real estate and loan closing process. Their Mission Statement is very simple. They strive for Excellence in Engineering! They take the time to incorporate the features which are meaningful in your use of the Landtech System. Their emphasis is to create the finest real estate settlement software available. If they accomplish that goal, then other pieces can be fashioned around that foundation! Contact us for a complete discussion and demonstration of Landtech. They will be happy to accommodate you in your endeavor to implement the finest technology available.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Literrater is a social network that has a community that attempts to connect readers and writers as a book is being written. This is to allow writers to focus on writing their book instead of writing it in isolation. Literrater appears to apply a startup mentality to writers, providing them with a means to get feedback and test ideas early so that the author can pivot early. It also lets authors gain traction on the writing as they write, potentially converting those contributors/readers into future consumers. Literrater also has social features for readers that are very similar to Goodreads, with the exception of the rating system. The rating system is from 1 to 100 and also allows users to rate or find a book by characteristics such as action, romance, mystery, quirkiness or mature attributes like sex, violence, profanity or horror. As with most social networks Literrater has user profiles and an activity feed based on the people someone has followed.
